title.narrative: By 2021, enhanced capacity for child poverty and equity analysis

description.narrative: Using LSIS-II data, UNICEF supported a Multiple Overlapping Deprivation Analysis which analyses the unmet needs and rights of children under age 18 in Lao PDR. One of the objectives of the MODA is to support the Government to have the baseline information for child poverty to track progress in Target 1.2 of the SDG 1, with the aim of reducing the percentage of children who are multi-dimensionally deprived according to the national definition by half by 2030. The report provides comprehensive analysis of linkages and status of implementation of other child-related SDGs. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
